2500|$|Two days later, Bess {{returns to}} Catfish Row {{in a state}} of delirium. When she recovers, she remembers what happened. Feeling that she betrayed <b>Porgy,</b> she begs his forgiveness. She admits she is unable to resist Crown [...] and asks <b>Porgy</b> to protect her from him. Crown {{eventually}} returns to claim his woman, and when he draws his knife, <b>Porgy</b> strangles him. He is detained by the police merely to identify the body, but Sportin' Life, who has fed Bess cocaine, convinces her <b>Porgy</b> inadvertently will reveal himself to be the murderer. In her drugged state, she finally accepts his offer to take her to New York. When <b>Porgy</b> returns and discovers she is gone, he sets off to find her.|$|R
