50|$|Knobbed <b>porgies</b> have {{a fairly}} deep body with a steep profile, and a nape that {{projects}} noticeably in larger adults, later developing into a humped 'forehead'. They are similar in coloration to the Littlehead porgy, with silver to brass bodies with a rosy cast and violet snouts and cheeks. Knobbed <b>porgies</b> can be distinguished by blue lines present on a yellowish under color.|$|E
